              "id": "GMS-2016-54",
              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "GMS-2016-54: OWASP Top Ten 2017 Category A9 - Using Components with Known Vulnerabilities"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://scout.docker.com/v/GMS-2016-54?s=gitlab&n=jws&t=npm&vr=%3C3.0.0",
              "help": {
                "text": "Since \"algorithm\" isn't enforced in `jws.verify()`, a malicious user could choose what algorithm is sent to the server. If the server is expecting RSA but is sent HMAC-SHA with RSA's public key, the server will think the public key is actually an HMAC private key. This could be used to forge any data an attacker wants.\n",
                "markdown": "> Since \"algorithm\" isn't enforced in `jws.verify()`, a malicious user could choose what algorithm is sent to the server. If the server is expecting RSA but is sent HMAC-SHA with RSA's public key, the server will think the public key is actually an HMAC private key. This could be used to forge any data an attacker wants.\n\n|                                   |\n|Package         pkg:npm/jws@0.2.6  |\n|Affected range  <3.0.0             |\n|Fixed version   3.0.0              |\n"
