                "text": "CVE-2021-32822: OWASP Top Ten 2017 Category A9 - Using Components with Known Vulnerabilities"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://scout.docker.com/v/CVE-2021-32822?s=gitlab&n=hbs&t=npm&vr=%3E%3D0",
              "help": {
                "text": "The npm hbs package is an Express view engine wrapper for Handlebars. Depending on usage, users of hbs may be vulnerable to a file disclosure vulnerability. There is currently no patch for this vulnerability. hbs mixes pure template data with engine configuration options through the Express render API. By overwriting internal configuration options a file disclosure vulnerability may be triggered in downstream applications.\n",
                "markdown": "> The npm hbs package is an Express view engine wrapper for Handlebars. Depending on usage, users of hbs may be vulnerable to a file disclosure vulnerability. There is currently no patch for this vulnerability. hbs mixes pure template data with engine configuration options through the Express render API. By overwriting internal configuration options a file disclosure vulnerability may be triggered in downstream applications.\n\n|                                                                                                  |\n|Package                                                                        pkg:npm/hbs@4.2.0  |\n|Affected range                                                                 >=0                |\n|Fixed version                                                                  not fixed          |\n|[[CVSS Score 5.3] [CVSS Vector CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:L/I:N/A:N]]                     |\n"
