            {
              "id": "GMS-2020-4",
              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "GMS-2020-4: OWASP Top Ten 2017 Category A9 - Using Components with Known Vulnerabilities"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://scout.docker.com/v/GMS-2020-4?s=gitlab&n=crypto-js&t=npm&vr=%3E%3D3.3.0%2C%3C4.0.0",
              "help": {
                "text": "An attacker is able to guess generated digits due to insufficient entropy.\n",
                "markdown": "> An attacker is able to guess generated digits due to insufficient entropy.\n\n|                                                                                      |\n|Package                                                      pkg:npm/crypto-js@3.3.0  |\n|Affected range                                               >=3.3.0,<4.0.0           |\n|Fixed version                                                3.2.1, 4.0.0             |\n|[[CVSS Score 7.5] [CVSS Vector AV:N/AC:L/Au:N/C:P/I:P/A:P]]                           |\n"
