            {
              "id": "CVE-2015-9235",
              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2015-9235: Improper Input Validation"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://scout.docker.com/v/CVE-2015-9235?s=github&n=jsonwebtoken&t=npm&vr=%3C4.2.2",
              "help": {
                "text": "Versions 4.2.1 and earlier of `jsonwebtoken` are affected by a verification bypass vulnerability. This is a result of weak validation of the JWT algorithm type, occuring when an attacker is allowed to arbitrarily specify the JWT algorithm.\n\n\n\n\n## Recommendation\n\nUpdate to version 4.2.2 or later.\n",
                "markdown": "> Versions 4.2.1 and earlier of `jsonwebtoken` are affected by a verification bypass vulnerability. This is a result of weak validation of the JWT algorithm type, occuring when an attacker is allowed to arbitrarily specify the JWT algorithm.\n\n\n\n\n## Recommendation\n\nUpdate to version 4.2.2 or later.\n\n|                                            |\n|Package         pkg:npm/jsonwebtoken@0.4.0  |\n|Affected range  <4.2.2                      |\n|Fixed version   4.2.2                       |\n"
