            {
              "id": "GHSA-5mrr-rgp6-x4gr",
              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "GHSA-5mrr-rgp6-x4gr: Improper Neutralization of Special Elements used in a Command ('Command Injection')"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://scout.docker.com/v/GHSA-5mrr-rgp6-x4gr?s=github&n=marsdb&t=npm&vr=%3E%3D0.0.0",
              "help": {
                "text": "All versions of `marsdb` are vulnerable to Command Injection. In the `DocumentMatcher` class, selectors on `$where` clauses are passed to a Function constructor unsanitized. This allows attackers to run arbitrary commands in the system when the function is executed.\n\n\n## Recommendation\n\nNo fix is currently available. Consider using an alternative package until a fix is made available.\n",
                "markdown": "> All versions of `marsdb` are vulnerable to Command Injection. In the `DocumentMatcher` class, selectors on `$where` clauses are passed to a Function constructor unsanitized. This allows attackers to run arbitrary commands in the system when the function is executed.\n\n\n## Recommendation\n\nNo fix is currently available. Consider using an alternative package until a fix is made available.\n\n|                                       |\n|Package         pkg:npm/marsdb@0.6.11  |\n|Affected range  >=0.0.0                |\n|Fixed version   not fixed              |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "affected_version": ">=0.0.0",
                "cvssV3_severity": "CRITICAL",
                "fixed_version": "not fixed",
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:npm/marsdb@0.6.11"
                ],
                "security-severity": "9.1",
                "tags": [
                  "CRITICAL"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2019-10744",
              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2019-10744: Improperly Controlled Modification of Object Prototype Attributes ('Prototype Pollution')"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://scout.docker.com/v/CVE-2019-10744?s=github&n=lodash&t=npm&vr=%3C4.17.12",
              "help": {
                "text": "Versions of `lodash` before 4.17.12 are vulnerable to Prototype Pollution.  The function `defaultsDeep` allows a malicious user to modify the prototype of `Object` via `{constructor: {prototype: {...}}}` causing the addition or modification of an existing property that will exist on all objects.\n\n## Recommendation\n\nUpdate to version 4.17.12 or later.\n",
                "markdown": "> Versions of `lodash` before 4.17.12 are vulnerable to Prototype Pollution.  The function `defaultsDeep` allows a malicious user to modify the prototype of `Object` via `{constructor: {prototype: {...}}}` causing the addition or modification of an existing property that will exist on all objects.\n\n## Recommendation\n\nUpdate to version 4.17.12 or later.\n\n|                                                                                                     |\n|Package                                                                        pkg:npm/lodash@2.4.2  |\n|Affected range                                                                 <4.17.12              |\n|Fixed version                                                                  4.17.12               |\n|[[CVSS Score 9.1] [CVSS Vector CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:H/A:H]]                        |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "affected_version": "<4.17.12",
                "cvssV3": 9.1,
                "cvssV3_severity": "CRITICAL",
                "cvssV3_vector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:H/A:H",
                "fixed_version": "4.17.12",
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:npm/lodash@2.4.2"
                ],
                "security-severity": "9.1",
                "tags": [
                  "CRITICAL"
                ]
              }
